One year into the Russia-Ukraine conflict, the city of Kyiv has almost returned to normal. For the local people, how has the conflict impacted their lives? CGTN anchor Xu Qinduo meets with local people at a First Aid Training Center to hear their stories. Trainee Lena says she returned to Kyiv from abroad after the conflict broke out to learn first aid so she could help save lives in the event of a missile attack. Ivan Nikolenko gave up his position as a government analyst to start the training center and help save lives. For the people of Kyiv, being prepared is crucial in helping them feel safe, and also to give them a sense of control in a situation where they have none.